{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"83941ad3-916c-48fa-bf3b-bbe6351cd279","content":"The directory is empty — there's no workflow file to inspect. No worries, here's a general guide for switching from `secrets.NUGET_API_KEY` to **NuGet trusted publishing (OIDC)**:\n\n---\n\n### 1. Configure your NuGet.org package for trusted publishing\n\nOn **nuget.org → Manage Package → Trusted Publishers**, add a new GitHub Actions publisher:\n- **Repository owner** — your GitHub org/user\n- **Repository name** — the repo name\n- **Workflow filename** — e.g. `publish.yml`\n- *(Optional)* **Environment** — e.g. `nuget` (recommended)\n\n### 2. Update your GitHub Actions workflow\n\n**Before (API key):**\n```yaml\n- run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg -k ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }} -s https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\n**After (OIDC trusted publishing):**\n```yaml\npermissions:\n  id-token: write   # Required for OIDC token\n\n# Optional but recommended: tie to a GitHub environment\nenvironment: nuget\n\nsteps:\n  - uses: actions/setup-dotnet@v4\n\n  # Request a short-lived token from NuGet via OIDC\n  - uses: dotnet/nuget-publish@v1\n\n  # Push using the token injected by the previous step\n  - run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg -s https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\n### Key changes\n\n| Item | Old | New |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Authentication** | `secrets.NUGET_API_KEY` | OIDC `id-token` permission + `dotnet/nuget-publish` action |\n| **Secret rotation** | Manual | Not needed — tokens are ephemeral |\n| **Permissions block** | Not required | `id-token: write` required |\n| **nuget.org config** | API key scoped to package | Trusted publisher entry linked to repo + workflow |\n\n### 3. Clean up\n- Remove the `NUGET_API_KEY` secret from your repo/org settings once OIDC publishing is verified.\n\nIf you share your workflow file, I can make the exact edits for you.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1098f9f1-eaee-42a5-b102-375bf3c12ea0","outputTokens":546},"id":"df13c2a3-1340-4a45-bfc8-90e9afbb8ca9","timestamp":"2026-04-04T00:37:01.808Z","parentId":"a55f7321-2079-49a8-b3ef-1afe4b4b68e7"}
